==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flier
<hw>Fli"er</hw> <pr>(fl⟦imac⟧"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Form
<er>Fly</er>, <pos>v.</pos>; cf. <er>Flyer</er>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who flies or flees; a runaway; a fugitive.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A fly. See <er>Fly</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>, 9, and 13 <sd>(b)</sd>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Spinning)</fld> <def>See <er>Flyer</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>, 5.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>See <er>Flyer</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>, 4.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>An a⟦eum⟧roplane or flying machine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flight</ent>⟦br⟧
